                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18360229-807-offence-1 t18360229-name-970"></join>William Heath</persName>, from his person.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18360229-name-971" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18360229-name-971" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360229-name-971" type="surname" value="HEATH"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360229-name-971" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM HEATH</persName>
                  </hi>. I live at Alton, in Hampshire—I have retired from business—I was in the road, walking toward Stamford-hill, on the 4th of March, and slung my great coat over my umbrella across my shoulder, hanging it behind me—the prisoner came up, and walked with me a con<lb></lb>siderable distance—he overtook me, and we walked together I suppose a mile and half—I occasionally talked to him—he was quite a stranger to me—he was walking abreast of me—when I was opposite a lane on the Stamford-road, I felt a twitch, and turned round, and he was running away with the coat—there was a neck handkerchief in one pocket, and a hat cover in other—I followed him a little way, and thought it useless to follow him further—I called out "Stop thief" two or three times—I went to the station-house afterwards, and saw the prisoner, and the coat; the handkerchief and hat-cover were in the pocket.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner</hi>. I picked it up. <hi rend="italic">Witness</hi>. He picked it off my umbrella—he did not pick it up.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18360229-name-972" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18360229-name-972" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360229-name-972" type="surname" value="SKITTER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360229-name-972" type="given" value="EDWARD"></interp>EDWARD SKITTER</persName>
                  </hi>. I am going on for ten years old, and am the son of John Skitter, a coachman, in Lamb-place, Kingsland-road—I saw Mr. Heath carrying a great coat on his umbrella at the top of the Church-lane—I saw prisoner snatch the coat off the gentleman's shoulder, and run down Church-lane—it was on the umbrella—there were several boys about—we gave chase, and ran after him—one boy caught hold of his sleeve, and he pushed him off, and got out of our sight—we went the front way towards Kingsland—I saw the policeman and told him, he pulled off his coat and cape, and we held them while he ran after the prisoner—I am sure he is the man.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18360229-name-973" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18360229-name-973" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360229-name-973" type="surname" value="COOTE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360229-name-973" type="given" value="JOSEPH"></interp>JOSEPH COOTE</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a policeman. I pursued the prisoner—I found the coat in Shacklewell-lane—I went there in consequence of information from Skitter, and several other boys—Arnold pursued the prisoner, and another officer took him.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18360229-name-974" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18360229-name-974" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360229-name-974" type="surname" value="ARNOLD"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360229-name-974" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM ARNOLD</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a policeman. I pursued the prisoner, but did not take him—I saw him in Shacklewell-lane at a quarter past four o'clock. when I was on duty—he was walking—I asked him what he had gather—he had the coat under his arm—he made no answer—I asked him againhe turned round, and said it was his own coat—I asked him</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183602290186"></xptr>
               <p>to let me took at it—he threw it towards me, jumped over a ditch, and ran off—I pursued him nearly a quarter of a mile, calling"Stop thief"—my brother officer heard me, and he met him in a field—I never lost sight of him.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18360229-name-975" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18360229-name-975" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360229-name-975" type="surname" value="AYRES"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360229-name-975" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN AYRES</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable N</hi> 218.) I stopped the prisoner is a p; ploughed field on Hackney-downs—hearing a cry of "Stop thief" I ran, and saw him crossing the field—I got within a rod of him, and he gave himself up to me—I took him—the officer who was pursuing him said he sus<lb></lb>pected he had stolen a coat—my brother officer said, we must find the owner of the coat, and he said, "D—it, I hope not."</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18360229-name-976" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18360229-name-976" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360229-name-976" type="surname" value="HEATH"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360229-name-976" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM HEATH</persName>
                  </hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">re-examined</hi>. I am certain it did not fall off my umbrella—it was partly resting on my shoulder—this is my coat.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence</hi> The coat, when I met it, was on the ground—I may have had it a minute in my possession—I heard the cry of"Stop thief, "and in my flurry I ran with it.</p>
